extends ../../layout

block title
  title AI For Healthcare Bootcamp Fall 2018

block description
  meta(name='description', content='Accelerated learning at the intersection of AI and healthcare.')

block extrascripts
include ../../includes/profile

block content
  section#header
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-9
          img#aihc_headline(src="/programs/aihc-bootcamp.svg")
  section.gray
    .container
      .row
        .col-sm-4
          h3 Teaching Team
          +dp('Pranav Rajpurkar', 'phd', false, true)
          +dp('Anand Avati', 'phd', false, true)
          +dp('Jeremy Irvin', 'ms', false, true)
          +dp('Tony Duan', 'ms', false, true)
          +dp('Andrew Ng', 'prof', false, true)
          +dp('Nigam Shah', 'prof', false, true)
          +dp('Matt Lungren', 'prof', false, true)
          +dp('Curt Langlotz', 'prof', false, true)
          +dp('Jeanne Shen', 'prof', false, true)
          +dp('Sanjay Basu', 'prof', false, true)
          +dp('Bhavik Patel', 'prof', false, true)
          +dp('Kristen Yeom', 'prof', false, true)
        .col-sm-8
          h2 Description
          p Over the course of Fall Quarter 2018, our bootcamp will cover a large breadth of topics at the intersection of artificial intelligence and healthcare. Students will take a dive into cutting-edge research in radiology, pathology, electronic health records, mental health, and public health, working closely with Ph.D. students and each other.
          h2 Timeline
          ul
            li Applications due TBD.
            li Interviews and selections TBD. 
            li Bootcamp starts first day of Fall Quarter.
          h2 Requirements
          ul
            li Must be a full-time Stanford student.
            li Should have taken CS229/CS230/CS224N/CS231N or equivalent.
            li Proficiency in Python.
          h2 Commitment
          ul
            li
              | Be able to register for 6 or more independent research units for this bootcamp. 
              | This level of commitment is not consistent with working as an RA or on other research projects simultaneously. However, we promise you will learn a lot from this experience.
            li
              | Be present at the bootcamp venue 5+ hours per day every day.
            li
              | Continue AI Research in the lab in Winter 2018-2019.
          h2 Previous Cohorts
          ul
            li
              a(href="/programs/aihc-bootcamp-spring2018") Spring 2017-2018
            li
              a(href="/programs/aihc-bootcamp-winter2018") Winter 2017-2018
            li
              a(href="/programs/aihc-bootcamp-fall2018") Fall 2017-2018
  section.bg-primary
    .container
      .row
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-4
          h2 We invite you to join the AI revolution in healthcare
          p Through your work in this program, we hope that you will improve human health, and perhaps even save countless lives.
          a.btn.btn-lg.btn-default(href="https://goo.gl/forms/4xpEQgCa2dskUakH3") Apply To Bootcamp
